{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T07:21:25.928Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch Normalization (Batch Norm)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a technique that normalizes the inputs to each layer "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "across the mini-batch"}, {"type": "text", "text": " during training, stabilizing the distribution of layer inputs and enabling faster, more stable training of deep neural networks. Introduced in 2015, it's now a standard component in most deep learning architectures."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Batch Norm — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Batch Norm Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batch Norm normalizes activations "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "for each feature dimension"}, {"type": "text", "text": " across all examples in a mini-batch:"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Take activations"}, {"type": "text", "text": " from a layer for a batch of examples"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Calculate mean and variance"}, {"type": "text", "text": " across that batch (per feature)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Normalize"}, {"type": "text", "text": " each activation: subtract mean, divide by standard deviation"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scale and shift"}, {"type": "text", "text": " using learnable parameters γ (gamma) and β (beta)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why It Matters: The Problem It Solves"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Internal Covariate Shift (ICS)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "During training, as weights in one layer update, the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "inputs to subsequent layers change distribution"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". This creates:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Layer interference"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Each layer's input distribution shifts as earlier layers train"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Slower training"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Network must constantly adapt to new distributions"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sensitivity to initialization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Poor initialization makes ICS worse"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Need for careful tuning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Learning rate, initialization, architecture all need balancing"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch Norm fixes this"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": By normalizing inputs to each layer, it ensures every layer sees a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "stable distribution"}, {"type": "text", "text": " regardless of what earlier layers do."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Batch Norm Works: The Math"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For a mini-batch of "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "m"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " examples with input dimension "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "d"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step 1: Compute Mean and Variance (per feature)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For feature "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "k"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " across the batch:\n\\[\n\\mu_k = \\frac{1}{m} \\sum"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{i=1}^m x"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{i,k}\n\\]\n\\[\n\\sigma_k^2 = \\frac{1}{m} \\sum"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{i=1}^m (x"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{i,k} - \\mu_k)^2\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step 2: Normalize"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\hat{x}_{i,k} = \\frac{x_{i,k} - \\mu_k}{\\sqrt{\\sigma_k^{2} + \\epsilon}}"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "where "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\epsilon"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a small constant (~1e-5) for numerical stability."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step 3: Scale and Shift (Learnable Transform)"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "y_{i,k} = \\gamma_k \\cdot \\hat{x}_{i,k} + \\beta_k"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why this step?"}, {"type": "text", "text": " - Normalization might remove useful information\n- γ and β allow the network to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "recover the original distribution"}, {"type": "text", "text": " if needed\n- These are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "learned during backpropagation"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Visual Example: Batch Norm vs. No Batch Norm"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Imagine a batch of 4 examples with 2 features:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Input batch (X):\n[2.0, 10.0]\n[4.0, 12.0]\n[6.0, 14.0]\n[8.0, 16.0]\n\nFeature 1 mean: μ₁ = (2+4+6+8)/4 = 5\nFeature 1 variance: σ₁² = ((2-5)² + (4-5)² + (6-5)² + (8-5)²)/4 = 5\n\nNormalized feature 1:\n[2-5]/√(5+ε) ≈ -1.34\n[4-5]/√(5+ε) ≈ -0.45\n[6-5]/√(5+ε) ≈  0.45\n[8-5]/√(5+ε) ≈  1.34\n\n(Now mean=0, variance≈1)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "After normalization: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feature 1 has mean 0, variance 1"}, {"type": "text", "text": " regardless of original scale."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Benefits of Batch Norm"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why It Happens"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Faster training"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stabilizes gradients → higher learning rates possible"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reduces sensitivity to initialization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Normalization masks poor weight choices"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Acts as regularizer"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mini-batch statistics add noise → reduces overfitting"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reduces need for dropout"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batch Norm's regularization often suffices"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Enables deeper networks"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Prevents activation saturation/vanishing"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Batch Norm Uses Mini-Batch Statistics"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch Norm normalizes across the batch dimension"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (not within a sample):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For a CNN layer with shape (batch_size, channels, height, width):\n├─ Normalize each channel independently\n├─ Compute mean/var across: batch_size × height × width\n└─ Output: same shape, normalized per channel"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Batch Norm treats each "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "feature dimension"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (e.g., each channel in CNN) independently, normalizing across all examples in the batch."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Training vs. Testing: Critical Difference"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "During Training"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "batch statistics"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (mean/var from current mini-batch)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batch statistics are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "noisy"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → this noise acts as regularization"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "γ and β are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "learned"}, {"type": "text", "text": " via backpropagation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "During Testing (Inference)"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "population statistics"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (mean/var from entire training set)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Compute running averages during training:"}]}]}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\mu_{\\text{train}} = \\frac{1}{T} \\sum_{t=1}^T \\mu_t, \\quad \\sigma_{\\text{train}}^2 = \\frac{1}{T} \\sum_{t=1}^T \\sigma_t^{2}"}}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No noise → deterministic output"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why different?"}, {"type": "text", "text": " - Training: batch stats introduce noise (regularization)\n- Testing: need consistent, reproducible predictions"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batch Norm vs. Layer Norm"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batch Norm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Layer Norm"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Normalization direction"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Across "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "examples"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in batch"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Across "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "neurons"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in one sample"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use case"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CNNs, MLPs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transformers, LSTMs"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch size dependency"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Yes (needs consistent batch size)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ No (works with batch=1)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small batch problem"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Noisy stats with small batches"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No problem"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Analogy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Grading students relative to class average"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Grading student based on own performance"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "When to use each"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch Norm"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": CNNs, feedforward networks, consistent batch sizes\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Layer Norm"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Sequential models (LSTMs, transformers), small/dynamic batches"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Practical Implementation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "PyTorch"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch.nn as nn\n\n# For fully connected layers\nmodel = nn.Sequential(\n    nn.Linear(128, 256),\n    nn.BatchNorm1d(256),  # Normalize 256 features\n    nn.ReLU(),\n    nn.Linear(256, 128),\n    nn.BatchNorm1d(128),\n    nn.ReLU()\n)\n\n# For CNNs\nmodel = nn.Sequential(\n    nn.Conv2d(3, 64, 3),\n    nn.BatchNorm2d(64),   # Normalize 64 channels\n    nn.ReLU(),\n    nn.Conv2d(64, 128, 3),\n    nn.BatchNorm2d(128),\n    nn.ReLU()\n)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TensorFlow/Keras"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from tensorflow.keras import layers, models\n\nmodel = models.Sequential([\n    layers.Dense(256, input_shape=(128,)),\n    layers.BatchNormalization(),  # Default for Dense\n    layers.ReLU(),\n    layers.Dense(128),\n    layers.BatchNormalization(),\n    layers.ReLU()\n])\n\n# For CNNs\nmodel = models.Sequential([\n    layers.Conv2D(64, 3, input_shape=(32, 32, 3)),\n    layers.BatchNormalization(),  # Default for Conv2D\n    layers.ReLU(),\n])"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Mistakes and Pitfalls"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mistake"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Problem"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Solution"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Using training mode during inference"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Output uses batch stats (noisy)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Set "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "model.eval()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in PyTorch"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch size = 1"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mean/var undefined (single sample)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Layer Norm instead"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch Norm before ReLU"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Can interfere with activation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Put Batch Norm "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "after"}, {"type": "text", "text": " activation (common) or before (some argue better)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small batch size"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Noisy statistics → poor training"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Increase batch size or use Layer Norm"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch Norm"}, {"type": "text", "text": " normalizes activations across the mini-batch for each feature dimension"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Four steps"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": compute mean/var → normalize → scale (γ) → shift (β)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Solves Internal Covariate Shift"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": stabilizes layer inputs regardless of earlier layer changes"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Benefits"}, {"type":